# Secure Enclave key directory for synrc/ca
#
# This directory is the canonical on-disk home for the macOS Secure Enclave
# (or equivalent hardware-backed) P-384 key associated with this CA instance.
#
# Contents written here by CA.SecureEnclave.provision/1:
#
#   se.label   — UTF-8 Keychain label string used by all NIF calls
#   pub.key    — raw uncompressed EC public key (04 || X || Y, 65 bytes)
#   pub.pem    — PEM-encoded SubjectPublicKeyInfo (for OpenSSL interop)
#
# The private key NEVER appears here.  It lives exclusively inside the
# Secure Enclave Processor and is referenced only via the label in se.label.
#
# NIST SP 800-53 references:
#   SC-12(4)  hardware encryption at rest (SEP UID key)
#   SC-28     private key never leaves SEP boundary
#   MP-4      key reference path: synrc/ecc/secp384r1/se/
